There are many ways to reverse String in Java. We can reverse String using StringBuffer, StringBuilder, iteration etc. 
Let's see the ways to reverse String in Java.

CODE 1:StringBuilder
public static String reverseString(String s){
    // code here
    StringBuilder sb=new StringBuilder(s);  
    sb.reverse(); 
    return sb.toString();
    
}

CODE 2: StringFormatter
public class TestStringFormatter {  
public static void main(String[] args) {  
    System.out.println(StringFormatter.reverseString("my name is khan"));  
    System.out.println(StringFormatter.reverseString("I am sonoo jaiswal"));      
    }  
}  

CODE 3: By Reverse Iteration
public class StringFormatter {  
public static String reverseString(String str){  
    char ch[]=str.toCharArray();  
    String rev="";  
    for(int i=ch.length-1;i>=0;i--){  
        rev+=ch[i];  
    }  
    return rev;  
}  
}  
